South African mineral processing equipment manufacturer Multotec Process Equipment has proven the economic impact of applying spiral concentration technology to high value minerals used in cellular phones and electric cars. “A number of customers mining minerals such as copper, lithium, tin and tantalite are already benefiting from using spirals to upgrade the value of their concentrate, either replacing their conventional processing technique or augmenting it,” says Multotec Process Equipment application engineer Graeme Smith. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 4, 2019 and will be published in full on 15 May 2019 You can read the
